ests specifically require it. I’m considering whether I should inspect the 2.0.0-M1 jar manifest and the existing configuration, as there might be JDK 25-related issues to address.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Preparing workflow for testing**\\n\\nI'm considering that while preparing the Forge workflow for the library issue, the driver might apply a deterministic setup beforehand, possibly recognizing the existing test scaffold. I need to determine if there's additional setup required beyond the normal generated scaffold. The existing build.gradle includes jvmArgs, but I wonder if the new generated one might change those. Should I also advise on setting add-exports if we're testing DnsSettings? The setup options might involve configuring environment or system properties in agent guidance.\"}]}"}, {"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"action\": \"no_action\",\n  \"summary\": \"No concrete extra setup is needed: org.apache.pekko:pekko-actor_2.13:2.0.0-M1 resolves to only scala-library and Typesafe Config, and normal classic actor/serialization usage is in-process with the pekko-actor artifact and no Docker service or required environment/system property.\",\n  \"deterministic_setup\": [],\n  \"agent_guidance\": \"\",\n  \"risks\": [\n    \"The observed failure is caused by tests using removed classic TypedActor APIs such as org.apache.pekko.actor.TypedActor, TypedActorExtension, and TypedProps; adding a dependency is not the right fix for pekko-actor_2.13 coverage.\",\n    \"The separate pekko-actor-typed_2.13 artifact contains the modern typed actor API, but adding it would broaden the test target beyond pekko-actor_2.13 and is not required for meaningful coverage of this library.\",\n    \"Existing DnsSettings-style coverage may require retaining the current --add-exports=java.base/sun.net.dns=ALL-UNNAMED JVM/native-image argument, but general meaningful coverage is reachable without introducing new setup.\"\n  ]\n}", "textSignature": "{\"v\":1,\"id\":\"msg